## ControlNet pose

ControlNet pose refers to a technique that uses the OpenPose model to extract a human's skeletal pose from an input image and then uses that pose to guide an AI image generator, like Stable Diffusion

## Wan2.2 Fun VACE

Wan2.2 Fun VACE isn’t just another model update — it’s a framework shift. It combines the power of VAE conditioning with ControlNet pose and mask editing in one streamlined pipeline, making complex edits feel almost effortless. For creators tired of juggling multiple tools or drowning in VRAM usage, this offers a smarter, modular way forward.

## VAE

A variational autoencoder (VAE) is a technique used to improve the quality of AI-generated images you create with the text-to-image model Stable Diffusion. VAE encodes the image into a latent space and then that latent space is decoded into a new, higher-quality image

## Wan VACE Fun

Wan2.2-Fun-14B video control weights support different control conditions, such as:
- Canny, Depth, Pose, MLSD, etc., 
- and also support the use of trajectory control.
##
------------------------------------------------------

- Supports video prediction of multiple resolutions (512, 768, 1024)
- Trained at 81 frames per second, and supports multi-language prediction.
